Admonition/Callout Transformation (convert_admonitions)
One of the most significant changes is the conversion of Docusaurus admonitions (which use a triple-colon syntax) to Quarto‚Äôs standard Callout blocks (which use a quadruple-colon syntax with a class identifier).
The convert_admonitions function uses a regular expression (Regex::new(r‚Äù^:::()+(.*)$‚Äú)) to identify the opening tag and extract the type and optional title.
